## When Making Changes

### Adding Features
1. Identify whether it's frontend (Next.js), backend (FastAPI), or both
2. Update relevant Makefile targets if you add new commands
3. Test on both synthetic and real databases
4. Document in `docs/` if it affects setup or deployment

### Schema Changes
- Run `npm run db:sync` after modifying `prisma/schema.prisma`
- This pushes the schema and regenerates Prisma Client
- If using Vercel backend, migration happens automatically on next deploy

### Python Backend Changes
- Run `make check` in the `backend/` directory to lint
- Run `make test` or `make test-agents` to verify
- Backend Makefile mirrors frontend patterns

### Tests
- Run `npm run check` (frontend) to lint/type-check
- Run `make check` in `backend/` (Python) to lint
- Always run before committing

